# Migration Conventions

## Migrations Are an Append-Only Record

Never edit a migration that has been committed. It has been run in production.
Create a new migration to change the schema.

## Reversibility First

Use `def change` for operations Rails can automatically reverse (add_column,
create_table, add_index, add_foreign_key). Use `def up` / `def down` for
irreversible changes. Raise `ActiveRecord::IrreversibleMigration` in `down`
only when data is genuinely destroyed and cannot be recreated.

```ruby
# Good â€” reversible
class AddPublishedAtToArticles < ActiveRecord::Migration[8.0]
  def change
    add_column :articles, :published_at, :datetime
    add_index :articles, :published_at
  end
end
```

## Database Constraints Are the Source of Truth

Enforce integrity at the database level. Model validations are for error
messages, not data safety.

```ruby
# Migration â€” source of truth
add_index :users, :email, unique: true
add_foreign_key :articles, :users, column: :author_id
change_column_null :articles, :title, false
```

## Safe Operations on Live Tables

Adding a NOT NULL column to a table with existing rows without a default
will fail. The safe pattern: add nullable â†’ backfill â†’ add constraint across
two deploys. See **`skills/writing-migrations/references/patterns.md`**.

Removing a column: tell ActiveRecord to ignore it first (Deploy 1), then
remove it (Deploy 2). See **`skills/writing-migrations/references/patterns.md`**
Â§ Removing Columns.

Adding an index on a large Postgres table: use `algorithm: :concurrently`
with `disable_ddl_transaction!` to avoid a full table lock.

## Separate Schema Changes from Data Migration

Data migrations (backfills) belong in a separate migration file or a rake
task â€” not mixed with DDL. Schema changes run instantly; data migrations
can take hours on large tables.

## Naming

Names are the permanent record. Be specific:
`add_published_at_to_articles`, `remove_legacy_status_from_users`,
`add_unique_index_to_users_on_email`.

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Instead |
|-------------|---------|
| Editing a past migration | New migration |
| `add_column null: false` on existing table with no default | Add nullable â†’ backfill â†’ add constraint |
| DDL and DML (backfill) in the same migration | Separate files |
| `add_index` without `algorithm: :concurrently` on large Postgres table | Concurrent index with `disable_ddl_transaction!` |
| `rename_column` on a live app | Three-step: add â†’ dual-write â†’ remove |
| Hardcoded IDs or seeds in migrations | Seeds file or separate rake task |
